The Telegraph - Calcutta : Nation
		 Monday, January 19, 2004 				 Bank boost for Valley
																								Jammu, Jan. 18: The Asian Development Bank (ADB) is handing out an emergency loan of $350 million to help Jammu and Kashmir rebuild infrastructure damaged and destroyed during 14 years of insurgency, reports our correspondent.																								A team led by Alex K. Jorgensen, head of the banks urban development department, has met Muzaffar Hussain Baig, minister for finance and planning, and informed him that the loan would be made available from June 2004. The whole amount will be remitted by 2007.																								Jorgensen was accompanied by Debashish Bhattacharjee, also of the urban development department, and Anil Motwani of the transport department.																								Besides the emergency loan, ADB is considering giving regular loans for upgrading power generation facilities, environment conservation and improvement of social services. 
